Our Story

Where it started
Kin began with a simple idea: a neighbourhood place where good coffee and good company come easily. We opened our doors with a battered espresso machine, a handful of tables, and a garden we couldn't quite believe came with the lease. Years on, the garden's grown wild and lovely, the machine's been upgraded, and the idea's stayed exactly the same.

How we do things
We roast for flavour, not fashion. We bake what we'd want to eat ourselves. And we've never been in a hurry to turn a table — if you've found a sunny corner and a second flat white feels right, that's the whole point. Come as you are, stay as long as you like.

Upcoming Events
Mother's Day
Mother's Day at Kin — Sunday morning, in the garden. Treat the mum in your life to a long, lazy brunch under the vines. We'll be running a special menu, fresh flowers on every table, and a little something on the house for every mum. Bookings recommended — this one fills up fast.

Jazz Night
Live Jazz Saturday — Last Saturday of the month, from 7pm. A trio, a glass of something good, and the garden lit up for the evening. No cover charge, kitchen open late, and the kind of easy night that makes you forget to check your phone. Pull up a chair.

Weekly Specials

Wednesday Pizza Night
Wood-fired, hand-stretched, and best shared. Every Wednesday from 5pm we fire up the oven for a rotating line-up of pizzas — plus a few classics that never leave. Two for one on the house reds till close.

Thursday Steak & Beer
A proper steak, chips, and a cold local beer for one tidy price. Thursdays from 6pm, while it lasts. Get in early — the good cuts go quick.

Happy Hour

Happy Hour
Every weekday, 4–6pm. Knock-off drinks done right: house wines, tap beers, and a short list of spritzes, all at neighbourhood prices. Snacks from the bar menu to match. The garden's at its best in the late afternoon light — we'd hate for you to miss it.